{"id": "duc04-testb-49:9#29", "contents": "The Clinton administration defends the IMF, arguing that its role in preventing a global economic meltdown has been crucial. Deputy Treasury Secretary Lawrence Summers told Congress that the situation would have been much worse without the IMF's program and finance. However, many Republicans and some Democrats remain unconvinced, and the House of Representatives recently defeated a measure to provide the IMF with $18 billion in funding. The fate of the IMF's funding now hangs in the balance, with the Senate and House set to resolve their budget differences in the coming days."}
